The paper deals with Linear Programming (LP) decoding of graphical binary codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The optimization problem formulated in the paper involves finding the lowest-weight pseudo-codeword, which is a problem in discrete optimization (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the structure of the code and the error-surface, which are topics in graph theory and combinatorics (cs.LG). The algorithm proposed in the paper is a heuristic, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper deals with the performance of the algorithm on a specific code over a specific channel, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY).
